 He finds solace in—[même jeu]; but on the other hand [three-quarters of a line turned by means of quotes into a flat statement]; at times it seems to him that”—and here Linyov inadvertently extricated something more or less whole:

Days of ripening vines! In the avenues, blue-shaded statues.

The fair heavens that lean on the motherland’s shoulders of snow.



—and it was as if the voice of a violin had suddenly drowned the hum of a patriarchal cretin.

